def: A small wig for the top of the head; a toupee.

A term used in designating many parts otherwise unnamed; as,the innominate artery, a great branch of the arch of the aorta; theinnominate vein, a great branch of the superior vena cava. Innominatebone (Anat.), the great bone which makes a lateral half of the pelvisin mammals; hip bone; haunch bone; huckle bone. It is composed ofthree bones, ilium, ischium, and pubis, consolidated into one in theadult, though separate in the fetus, as also in many adult reptilesand amphibians.-- Innominate contracts (Law), in the Roman law, contracts without aspecific name.
Frequently; often. [Obs.]For whom I sighed have so oftensith. Gascoigne.
An aspect of the planets when they are distant from each otherthe twelfth part of a circle, or thirty degrees. Hutton.
Not tamed; untamed; savage; wild. [Obs.] J. Salkeld.

A phenol derivative of cymene, C10H13.OH, isomeric withcarvacrol, found in oil of thyme, and extracted as a whitecrystalline substance of a pleasant aromatic odor and strongantiseptic properties; -- called also hydroxy cymene.
The common newt; -- called also asker, eft, evat, and ewt.
Increase; addition; surplus. [Obs.] Sir H. Wotton.
Divine nature or essence; deity; godhead.
A column of igneous rock formed by congelation of lava in theconduit of a volcano and later exposed by the removal of surroundingrocks.
